aS'We are not going to dwell on Melania Trump\xe2\x80\x99s flying to flood-ravaged Texas in stilettos, or sneakers, here. But nature abhors a vacuum, and the first lady\xe2\x80\x99s fans and critics focus on her costumes in part because, so far, that\xe2\x80\x99s about all they see of Melania Trump. In the back-to-work spirit of Labor Day, let\xe2\x80\x99s reflect on Mrs. Trump\xe2\x80\x99s plans as first lady now that she\xe2\x80\x99s settled in the White House and Barron, her only child, heads back to school.\nAmerican first ladies occupy an unpaid job in the middle of a political minefield. \xe2\x80\x9cYou\xe2\x80\x99re reflecting not only on yourself and the administration; you\xe2\x80\x99re in a way seen as representative of all women,\xe2\x80\x9d says Lisa Kathleen Graddy, curator of American political history and women\xe2\x80\x99s political history at the Smithsonian\xe2\x80\x99s National Museum of American History. Americans expect their first ladies to be \xe2\x80\x9call things at all times: graceful, courteous, considerate, compassionate, diplomatic \xe2\x80\x94 but in an acceptable kind of way, not overblown, or hectoring. \xe2\x80\xa6 There are no written rules. You find those lines only when you cross them.\xe2\x80\x9d\nMrs. Trump\xe2\x80\x99s added burden is that besides helping to change the world, she has been expected to help change her husband. We\xe2\x80\x99ll get back to that.\nBorn in Slovenia, Melania Trump is the first foreign-born first lady to occupy the White House since Louisa Adams, the London-born wife of John Quincy Adams, who became first lady in 1825. Some first ladies use their perch to continue work they have already been interested in, as when Eleanor Roosevelt turned her longtime passion for politics into advocacy for human rights and a post-White House diplomatic career.\nMrs. Trump hasn\xe2\x80\x99t had much in the way of traditional job preparation, which puts her on par with most people in this inexperienced White House. Her previous jobs as a fashion model and QVC jewelry entrepreneur don\xe2\x80\x99t readily translate. Her interest in fashion contributed to last week\xe2\x80\x99s contretemps over her shoes. And her lawyers\xe2\x80\x99 reference, in two successful libel suits against \n, to the potential for her to start \xe2\x80\x9ca broad-based commercial brand in multiple product categories\xe2\x80\x9d while in the White House, reinforced the widely held belief that the Trumps see the presidency as a merchandising opportunity.\nStephanie Grisham, Mrs. Trump\xe2\x80\x99s spokeswoman, says that the first lady will announce her initiatives in her own good time, and that her devotion as a mother \xe2\x80\x94 she is essentially a single parent to 11-year-old Barron \xe2\x80\x94 provides hints of her next move. So, too, does her participation in a panel on opioid abuse this summer. \xe2\x80\x9cSept. is Nat\xe2\x80\x99l Alcohol&Drug Addiction Recovery Month. Together we can strengthen families&communities & beat addiction,\xe2\x80\x9d she \n on Friday.\nWhile her husband\xe2\x80\x99s Twitter account is a toxic dump, Mrs. Trump\xe2\x80\x99s is a pristine model of offered thanks, prayers, support for children and support for victims of disaster. After the neo-Nazi violence in Charlottesville, Va., she \n: \xe2\x80\x9cOur country encourages freedom of speech, but let\xe2\x80\x99s communicate w/o hate in our hearts. No good comes from violence. \n.\xe2\x80\x9d\nAs Hillary Clinton and Michelle Obama did with their children, Mrs. Trump is determined to shield Barron from a prying public. She has made her share of hospital and classroom visits, and in photographs she appears happier in the company of children \n of \xe2\x80\xa6 you know, the guy she \n to as, \xe2\x80\x9cSometimes I say I have two teenage boys at home.\xe2\x80\x9d Mrs. Trump has kept Mrs. Obama\xe2\x80\x99s garden because, as Ms. Grisham says, she knows Mrs. Obama loved it, and she appreciates its role in teaching kids to make healthy choices.\nWhich brings us to Mr. Trump, whose social media choices need work. After saying that combating cyberbullying is something she\xe2\x80\x99d like to work on, Mrs. Trump has made no headway in reforming the cyberbully in chief. She was criticized for seeming to defend her husband\xe2\x80\x99s grotesque \n assault on the television journalist Mika Brzezinski, when Ms. Grisham \n that \xe2\x80\x9cas the first lady has stated publicly in the past, when her husband gets attacked, he will punch back 10 times harder.\xe2\x80\x9d Ms. Grisham took responsibility for that one, saying it was a comment of Mrs. Trump\xe2\x80\x99s from the past, and \xe2\x80\x9cout of context.\xe2\x80\x9d\nFive-inch heels may not be enough to elevate Mrs. Trump from the muck flowing through this White House. But as we search every corner for people who are growing in the job, let\xe2\x80\x99s hope the first lady will provide the grace and normality that has been so lacking. But if she does, will Mr. Trump tolerate a wife who\xe2\x80\x99s more popular than he is?\n'
