aS'Myanmar, a Buddhist-majority country, has slaughtered civilians belonging to the Rohingya Muslim minority, leading more than 270,000 Rohingya to flee to to Bangladesh. \n, the de facto leader of \n and a Nobel Peace Prize laureate who once embodied the country\xe2\x80\x99s fight for democracy, has come under pressure for remaining silent about the minority\xe2\x80\x99s plight.\n'
