aS" Sunday\xe2\x80\x99s Primetime Emmy winners will take home shiny trophies and bask in congratulations, but their biggest payoff could come in a call from Netflix Inc (\n) or Amazon.com Inc (\n).  \nIn recent months, the two streaming networks have lured the makers of pioneering shows from broadcast and cable networks with big cash offers and promises of creative freedom. \n\xe2\x80\x9cNetflix, Amazon, Hulu and the like are really putting their money where their mouth is,\xe2\x80\x9d said Melissa Rosenberg, a former writer on Showtime\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cDexter\xe2\x80\x9d who moved to Netflix to create the dark superhero show \xe2\x80\x9cJessica Jones.\xe2\x80\x9d  \n\xe2\x80\x9cThey\xe2\x80\x99re paying creators, extraordinary actors, and for the budgets of shows equal or better than basic cable or network TV,\xe2\x80\x9d she said. \nSome of television\xe2\x80\x99s biggest names have deserted network and cable for streaming.  \nNetflix enticed Shonda Rhimes away from her longtime home on Walt Disney Co\xe2\x80\x99s (\n) ABC, where she developed hits like \xe2\x80\x9cGrey\xe2\x80\x99s Anatomy\xe2\x80\x9d and \xe2\x80\x9cScandal.\xe2\x80\x9d It also landed filmmakers Joel and Ethan Coen for a western anthology series after their success with a TV spinoff of their movie \xe2\x80\x9cFargo\xe2\x80\x9d on FX (\n). \nAmazon lured Matthew Weiner, who put AMC on the map with his Emmy award-winning \xe2\x80\x9cMad Men,\xe2\x80\x9d to develop an anthology series called \xe2\x80\x9cThe Romanoffs.\xe2\x80\x9d It also has brought on Robert Kirkman, the man behind the basic cable network\xe2\x80\x99s current most-watched show, \xe2\x80\x9cThe Walking Dead,\xe2\x80\x9d to create new shows.   \nNetflix, which received 91 Emmy nominations this year, has a shot at winning its first best drama series award with supernatural mystery \xe2\x80\x9cStranger Things\xe2\x80\x9d or British royal saga \xe2\x80\x9cThe Crown,\xe2\x80\x9d whose reported $130 million budget is the most expensive TV production ever. \nHulu\xe2\x80\x99s critically acclaimed \xe2\x80\x9cThe Handmaid\xe2\x80\x99s Tale\xe2\x80\x9d could bring the joint venture streaming platform its first major Emmys. \nCable and traditional television are still forces to be reckoned with, though. \n\xe2\x80\x9cTraditional media companies are scrambling, saying: \xe2\x80\x98How do we beat back so much money being thrown at TV?'\xe2\x80\x9d said Peter Csathy, chairman of media and technology advisory firm CREATV Media. \n\xe2\x80\x9cThe challenge is about compelling storytelling and keeping talent amid those forces,\xe2\x80\x9d he added. \nNBC\xe2\x80\x99s family drama \xe2\x80\x9cThis Is Us\xe2\x80\x9d could clinch the first best drama series Emmy for one of the four big U.S. broadcasters since 2006, and the Comcast-owned CMSCA.O network\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cSaturday Night Live\xe2\x80\x9d is expected to take home an armful of trophies. \nHBO (\n), which led the Emmy nominations with 111 nods, and FX have capitalized on the limited-series format that streaming platforms prefer, with shorter seasons, cinematic-style storytelling and A-list talent.  \nHBO\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cBig Little Lies,\xe2\x80\x9d starring Reese Witherspoon and Nicole Kidman, is a front-runner in this category, as is FX\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cFeud,\xe2\x80\x9d which pits Susan Sarandon opposite Jessica Lange.  \nHBO\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cThe Wizard of Lies\xe2\x80\x9d lured Robert De Niro to his first major TV role and Emmy nomination for playing disgraced financier Bernie Madoff. \nOne big attraction for broadcast television defectors is the creative freedom offered by streaming.  \n\xe2\x80\x9cNetwork (TV) is limited by what it can put on air, and it answers to advertisers, so there are a lot of limitations as to how far you can go, whether a character is likeable, edgy, racy,\xe2\x80\x9d said \xe2\x80\x9cJessica Jones\xe2\x80\x9d creator Rosenberg.  \nAnd all the networks are chasing the next \xe2\x80\x9cGame of Thrones,\xe2\x80\x9d HBO\xe2\x80\x99s popular Emmy-winning medieval fantasy series, which has become the pinnacle of prestige TV.   \n\xe2\x80\x9cEveryone is looking for a tent-pole show so that they can scream loud and proud to bring audiences and keep them there,\xe2\x80\x9d CREATV\xe2\x80\x99s Csathy said.   \n\xe2\x80\x9c\xe2\x80\x98Game of Thrones\xe2\x80\x99 is a poster child for breaking the rules in terms of storytelling and killing off lead characters with reckless abandon,\xe2\x80\x9d he said. \xe2\x80\x9cThat\xe2\x80\x99s something we traditionally have not seen in television.\xe2\x80\x9d \n"
